> Any idea how your block estimator ended up giving you estimates lower than your set min mempool feerate? Seems to me this requires you to change your min rate _after_ your estimator builds these estimates?

@instagibbs: As I understand it, the fee estimator in Bitcoin Core uses statistical analysis of previous transaction confirmation times to build up its estimates. The `mempoolminfee` reacts to current mempool conditions.

Suppose that there is a sudden spike in transaction traffic. Fees had been low for a while; the mempool had been close to empty. Suddenly, someone drops a million transactions onto the network. This will have no immediate effect on Bitcoin Core's fee estimator (sadly), but it will absolutely bump up `mempoolminfee` immediately.
